ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='The API tests pass and lint passes. shared-types has no tests and lin
t fails due to missing eslint config. But that might be pre-existing. However we
need to check if the shared-types package has tests or not; the PR didn\'t add a
ny. The lint issue is pre-existing. We should note it maybe.\n\nNow we need to c
heck Flutter side. Since flutter command is not available, we cannot run tests o
r analyze. We can still review code manually.\n\nWe need to check for missing pi
eces:\n\n- **docs/api-contracts/auth.yaml** is missing. The exec plan says it sh
ould be filled. The diff didn\'t include it, and the directory doesn\'t exist. T
his is a documentation sync issue.\n- **packages/shared-types/src/index.ts** was
updated with auth types. That looks correct.\n- **DB + API + Mobile**: DB migrat
ion is present, API is present, Mobile is present. Full chain seems okay.\n- **N
aming conventions**: \n  - NestJS: DTOs use `@IsString` etc. Good. \n  - Control
ler uses `AuthController`, Service uses `AuthService`. Good.\n  - Entity names: 
`UserEntity`, `UserProfileEntity`. Good.\n  - Migration name: `CreateUsersAndUse
rProfiles20250410000000`. The naming convention says `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS-Description
.ts`. The file name is `20250410000000-CreateUsersAndUserProfiles.ts`, which mat
ches. The class name is `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles20250410000000`, which is a b
it reversed but okay? The convention doesn\'t specify class name exactly, but ty
pical TypeORM uses `DescriptionYYYYMMDDHHMMSS`. This is fine.\n  - DB table name
s: `users`, `user_profiles`. Good. Columns are snake_case. Good.\n  - DB primary
keys: `char(36)`. Good.\n  - DB timestamps: `created_at`, `updated_at` present. 
Good.\n  - DB soft delete: `deleted_at` is not present. But the PRD/infrastructu
re might not require it for users? The DB design doc says each table must contai
n `deleted_at`. But the migration from infrastructure bootstrap might not have i
t. However this migration creates `users` and `user_profiles` without `deleted_a
t`. The DB design doc says "软删除：使用 deleted_at（nullable datetime），不直接
物理删除". This is a violation. We should flag it.\n- **API design**:\n  - `auth
.controller.ts` uses `@Body() dto: LoginDto`. Good.\n  - `logout` takes `@Header
s("authorization") authHeader: string` and extracts token manually. This is okay
but could use decorator. Not a big issue.\n  - `AuthService.login` does `findOrC
reateUser` and generates tokens. It updates `last_login_at`? The PRD says "登录
成功后更新 `users.last_login_at` 字段." But the UserEntity and migration do not 
have `last_login_at`. The service does not update it. This is a missing requirem
ent.\n  - `AuthService.getMe` returns `is_new_user` based on profile completenes
s. The PRD says `GET /auth/me` should be used to check profile completion. In th
e BLoC, after login, it calls `getMe` and uses `profile_complete`. That\'s okay.
\n  - `AuthService.generateTokens` sets `is_new_user: false` always, then `login
` overrides it. That\'s okay.\n  - `AuthService.refreshTokens` blacklists old re
fresh token and generates new ones. It also checks active JTI. Good.\n  - `AuthS
ervice.logout` blacklists access token and deletes refresh token. Good.\n  - Rat
e limiting for SMS: PRD says "同一手机号 1 分钟内最多请求 1 次验证码，1 小时内最
多 5 次". There is no SMS send endpoint implemented. The login page just starts 
a countdown. The PRD says MVP fixed code. The exec plan says `validateSmsCode` a
nd `seedSmsCode`. There is no actual send endpoint, so rate limiting is not appl
icable? But the PRD says "登录接口增加基础速率限制". However, there is no SMS se
nd endpoint. Maybe it\'s acceptable for MVP, but we can note it as missing.\n  -
`JwtAuthGuard` uses `jsonwebtoken` directly instead of `@nestjs/jwt` or `@nestjs
/passport`. That\'s okay but manual.\n  - `JwtAuthGuard` has `declare module "ex
press"` to extend Request. That\'s okay.\n  - `AllExceptionsFilter` catches ever
ything and returns `{code, message, data}`. It maps 401 to code 2001. Good.\n- *
*Contract consistency**:\n  - `shared-types/src/index.ts` defines `LoginRequest`
, `RefreshRequest`, `AuthResponse`, `UserResponse`.\n  - DTOs: `LoginDto` has `p
hone`, `sms_code`. `RefreshDto` has `refresh_token`. `AuthResponseDto` has `acce
ss_token`, `refresh_token`, `expires_in`, `is_new_user`. `UserResponseDto` has `
id`, `phone`, `is_new_user`, `profile_complete?`. This matches shared-types.\n  
- Mobile uses `Map<String, dynamic>` directly instead of generated models. The e
xec plan says "Mobile 登录页、Auth BLoC、SecureStorage、HTTP 拦截器" and "Mobile
使用 Dio + flutter_secure_storage". The design doc says "Model 字段命名必须与后
端 DTO 完全一致". Mobile uses raw maps. That\'s not ideal but maybe acceptable? 
However, the design doc says "所有 Model 使用 `freezed` + `json_serializable`". 
The mobile code does not define any models; it uses raw maps. This is a violatio
n of Flutter coding standards. Also, the `data` layer should use models. The rep
ository returns `Map<String, dynamic>`. The BLoC accesses fields like `data[\'ac
cess_token\']`. This is brittle and violates the "禁止在 Widget 中直接调用 Dio/h
ttp" (it\'s in repository, okay) and "禁止使用 dynamic 传递 API 数据" (the repos
itory uses `Map<String, dynamic>`, which is dynamic). So this is a violation.\n 
- There are no generated Dart models from OpenAPI because `docs/api-contracts/au
th.yaml` is missing. So the mobile can\'t use generated models. But they should 
at least define typed models manually.\n- **Mobile BLoC**:\n  - `AuthBloc` uses 
`AuthRepositoryImpl` directly in constructor default. This couples BLoC to imple
mentation, violating DI principle. The design doc says "依赖注入：get_it + injec
table". The BLoC should use `get_it` or at least accept interface. It does accep
t optional params, but default is concrete implementation. This is not ideal.\n 
- `AuthBloc._onTokenRefreshed` is empty. The interceptor handles it, but maybe i
t should emit a state. Not a big issue.\n  - `LoginPage` uses `BlocListener` ins
ide the widget tree (as a child of Column). That\'s okay but it\'s nested. It us
es `ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar` which requires a Scaffold ancest
or. The `LoginPage` returns a `Scaffold`, so it\'s fine.\n  - `LoginPage` uses `
TextStyle` with hard-coded fontSize 14 and 16. The design doc says "禁止在 page 
中写死设计 Token：所有颜色、字号、间距、圆角必须从 DesignTokens 读取". It uses `
DesignTokens` for colors and spacing, but for font sizes in Text widgets inside 
buttons it uses `const TextStyle(fontSize: 14)` and `TextStyle(fontSize: DesignT
okens.fontSizeHeadline...)`. The button text uses hard-coded fontSize 14 and 16.
That\'s a minor violation.\n  - `LoginPage` uses `ElevatedButton.styleFrom` with
`shape`. It doesn\'t use `SwButton` or design system atoms. The design doc says 
"设计系统组件必须以 Sw 为前缀". But using built-in widgets is not strictly prohi
bited if design system components don\'t exist yet. However, the design doc says
"新增组件必须在 Widgetbook 注册". Since they didn\'t add new components, just us
ing built-in is okay? But "禁止在 page 中写死设计 Token" suggests they should us
e design tokens. They mostly do, but font sizes in buttons are hard-coded.\n- **
Tests**:\n  - API has `auth.service.spec.ts` with 7 tests. It covers some core f
unctions. But it doesn\'t test `refreshTokens`, `login`, `getMe`, `invalidateOld
RefreshToken`. The exec plan says "测试 AuthService 的核心函数：validateSmsCode
、generateTokens、refreshTokens." But `refreshTokens` is missing. So test covera
ge is incomplete.\n  - BDD step definitions are all placeholder TODOs. They don\
't actually test anything. The PR includes the feature file (already existed may
be) but step definitions are empty. The exec plan says "建立 BDD 验收测试覆盖全
部用户故事". This is not fulfilled.\n  - Mobile has no widget or bloc tests. The
design doc says `flutter_test` should be used. None present.\n- **Docs sync**:\n
 - `docs/modules/auth.md` exists and is updated. Good.\n  - `docs/modules/INDEX.
md` already references auth.md. Good.\n  - `docs/api-contracts/auth.yaml` is mis
sing. The exec plan says it should be filled. This is a missing doc.\n  - The PR
D references `tests/bdd/auth_login.feature`, which exists. Good.\n- **Other issu
es**:\n  - `AuthInterceptor._clearTokensAndRedirect` only clears tokens, but doe
sn\'t redirect. It says "redirect" but there\'s no navigation. The interceptor c
an\'t navigate because it doesn\'t have context. It should perhaps emit an event
to AuthBloc or use a navigator key. But the PRD says "刷新失败：跳转登录页，清除
Token". In the interceptor, it just clears tokens. The app will likely redirect 
when next request fails or when BLoC detects. But it\'s not a full redirect. How
ever, in the BLoC, `AuthCheckRequested` will fail and emit `AuthUnauthenticated`
, which triggers router to go to login. But if a request fails with 401 while us
er is on a page, the interceptor clears tokens but the UI might stay until next 
request or manual navigation. This is a gap.\n  - `DioClient` uses `https://api.
social.world/api/v1` as baseUrl. But the API global prefix is `api/v1`. The cont
roller routes are `auth/login`. So the full URL would be `https://api.social.wor
ld/api/v1/auth/login`. That\'s okay.\n  - `AuthRepositoryImpl` uses `DioClient()
.dio` directly. This creates a new DioClient instance each time. It should be in
jected.\n  - `AuthRepositoryImpl.refresh` and `AuthInterceptor._refreshToken` bo
th post to `/auth/refresh`. The interceptor\'s `_refreshToken` uses `_dio.post(\
'/auth/refresh\')` without baseUrl issue.\n  - `AuthInterceptor.onError` resolve
s the original request with `handler.resolve(response)` and then retries pending
requests. But it resolves the original request before `_retryPendingRequests`. T
hat\'s okay. However, `_retryPendingRequests` uses `_dio.fetch` which is asynchr
onous and not awaited. If one of those fails, it just calls `reject`. That\'s ok
ay.\n  - `AuthInterceptor.onError` calls `handler.reject(err)` after `_rejectPen
dingRequests(err)` in the failure case. But it also calls `await _clearTokensAnd
Redirect()`. Since it\'s async, the handler.reject should be called after the aw
